<div class="row">
 <h2>SMSwallet Commands</h2>
 <p>Commands are not case-sensitve and are sent to the gateways via SMS/text.</p>
  <div class="col-sm-12 wbox"></div>
    <div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
      <!--address--> 
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
           <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#ADDRESS">
             ADDRESS
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="ADDRESS" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>The ADDRESS command returns the most recent bitcoin address associated to your SMSwallet account. With this bitcoin address, you can deposit bitcoins from another bitcoin wallet. If you don’t have any bitcoins, you can purchase them from <a href="www.localbitcoins.com">Localbitcoins</a> or <a href="www.coinbase.com">Coinbase</a>.</p>
            <div class="alert alert-warning">Recognized shorthand or misspellings, English (EN): address, addr, deposit, adr, adress</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!--balance-->
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#BALANCE">
              BALANCE
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="BALANCE" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>The balance command returns the current bitcoin value of your SMSwallet.</p>
            <p>The balance reported already reflects the potential transaction fee. Therefore it reflects the maximum amount of bitcoins that you can transfer to another person.</p>
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <td>System response</td><td>Implication</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Balance 12.048mBTC ($5.24)<br/>Reply ADDR, for Bitcoin address</td><td>You can SEND up to 12.048 worth of Bitcoins to another phone number or bitcoin address</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <label>*Bitcoin to US Dollar values, as of 5/4/2014</label>
            <div class="alert alert-warning">Recognized shorthand or misspellings, English (EN): balance, bal, blance, balnce</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!--send-->
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#SEND">
              SEND
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="SEND" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>The SEND command send bitcoins from your SMSwallet account to another SMSwallet or bitcoin wallet.</p>
            </p>The recipient does not need to have an account with us. If you send bitcoins to a phone number that does not have a SMSwallet account, one will be created for them and they will be notiﬁed.</p>
            <p><strong>Ensure that you typed the recipients phone number or bitcoin address correctly. Once sent, the transaction cannot be reversed.</strong></p>
            
            <h5>SEND command syntax</h5>
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <caption>SEND &lt;amount&gt;&lt;address&gt;[comment]</caption>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                 <tr>
                  <td>&lt;amount&gt;</td><td>The amount to send to the recipient. Use 12 to indicate 12mBTC, use 5USD to indicate sending bitcoins in the value of 5 US dollars. (You can use any of the 3 character currency code codes, such as PHP, EUR, …)</td>
                </tr>
                 <tr>
                  <td>&lt;address&gt;</td><td>The destination address to send the bitcoins. Can be either a phone number or a bitcoin address. Phone numbers may have spaces or not.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>[comment]</td><td>Optional comment, up to 40 characters. Messages that are too long will be shortend.</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table> 

            <h5>SEND command examples</h5>
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <caption>Sending bitcoin domestically (assuming a US SMSwallet user)</caption>
                <tr>
                 <td>Example</td><td>Command explanation</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>SEND 1USD 6165551234</td><td>This request the system to send 1 US dollar worth of bitcoin to the US phone number 6165551234</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <caption>Sending bitcoin overseas (assuming a US SMSwallet user)</caption>
                <tr>
                  <td>Example</td><td>Command explanation</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>SEND 44PHP +63 912 123 1234</td><td>This requests the system to send 44 Philippine Pesos worth of bitcoin to the PH phone number +63 912 555 1234</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <caption>Sending with shorthand</caption>
                <tr>
                  <td>Example</td><td>Command explanation</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>6.3 6165551234</td><td>This requests the system to send 6.3 mBTC to the phone number 6165551234</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <table class="table table-striped">
              <thead>
                <caption>Sending to a bitcoin address</caption>
                <tr>
                  <td>Example</td><td>Command explanation</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>SEND 12USD 19xeDDxhahx4f32WtBbPwFMWBq28rrYVoh</td><td>This requests the system to send 12USD worth of bitcoin to the bitcoin address 19xeDDxhahx4f32WtBbPwFMWBq28rrYVoh</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table> 

            <div class="alert alert-warning">Recognized shorthand or misspellings, English (EN): send, sending, sent
            </div>        
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!--transaction-->
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#TRANSACTION">
