          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="TRANSACTION" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>The transaction command returns the history of your last three transactions.</p>
            <div class="alert alert-warning">Recognized shorthand or misspellings, English (EN): transactions, txns, trans, tran</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!--pin-->
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
          <h4 class="panel-title">
            <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#PIN">
              PIN:<br/> Setup your Secret PIN
            </a>
          </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="PIN" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>The PIN command sets up the Security PIN for your account. If a Security PIN is not already set up, the system will call you and guide you through the process. If the Security PIN is already set up, the system will call you, confirm your existing Security PIN, and then guide you through setting up a different security PIN.</p>
            <p>The Security PIN is a 4-digit code that you assign. It protects your account from unauthorized spending. When you receive the voice call to setup your PIN, the system will prompt you to dial your 4-digit code, followed by the hash key (#).</p>
            <p>Currently the Security PIN is required if you try to SEND more than 12mBTC (2014/05/04 $5.25) in one day. In the future, you will be able to adjust this amount.</p>
            <div class="alert alert-warning">Recognized shorthand or misspellings, English (EN): pin, voice</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
